- make a "top-ten list" of helpful design and programming rules. Hint $2

1. imagine ideas(concepts) in code
2. don`t focus on unnecessary
3. put dependencies between the ideas in code
4. isolated ideas should be isolated code parts
5. choose solutions that will be checked static
6. simple ideas implement simply
7. use standard library instead of creating your own
8. C++ is not widen C
9. use move semantics
10. use templates instead of adding a lot of new types
